peopleAlsoAsk.question: How can you tell how old a Budweiser bottle is?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: Much of the time, the mold seam height indicates how old the bottle is. Machine-produced bottles from 1905 through the 1920s displayed higher, thicker mold seams compared to later machine-made bottles. As technology progressed, the seams grew thinner until they reached a hair's thickness.
